Definition of Personal Data
The personal data is defined as any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person. It makes a direct reference to sound and image (Article 1 of the Digital Code).
Definition of Sensitive Personal Data
Pursuant to Article 1 of the Digital Code, the following personal data is considered 'sensitive' and is subject to specific processing conditions: personal data revealing racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs; trade union membership; genetic data; and health-related data; data concerning a person's sex life or sexual orientation, prosecution to criminal and administrative penalties.Last modified 10 Jan 2022
				
			